<h2 class="nounderline"><a name="maincontent">Transition and Employment Specialist</a></h2>
<p>
<strong>POSITION</strong>: Transition and Employment Specialist<br />
<strong>SUPERVISORS</strong>: Barb Ziemke, Gretchen Godfrey; Co-Directors<br />
<strong>STATUS</strong>: Full time, salaried monthly, exempt status</p>

<p>This role is to help promote high expectations for youth with disabilities as they transition from high school to adult living in the community, in the areas of post-secondary education, employment, and independent living. </p>
<h3><strong>Specific Duties and Responsibilities</strong>:</h3>
<ol>
  <li>Present at local, state, and national conferences, events, and workshops on transition-related topics.</li>
  <li>Provide individual assistance, information, and guidance to families and students through phone, email and web conferencing on transition-related issues.</li>
  <li>Collaborate with professionals from agencies serving youth and young adults with disabilities.</li>
  <li>Write and develop materials to support families of students with disabilities on transition-related supports, including articles, blogs, and promotional outreach.</li>
  <li>Contribute content to website, including resources, articles, stories, and news.</li>
  <li>Maintain the project deadlines and meet project goals in a timely manner. </li>
  <li>Assist with project data collection and evaluation. </li>
  <li>Other tasks as needed.</li>
</ol>

<h3>Requirements:</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree or related experience</li>
  <li>Expertise or desire to learn about employment and education rights and opportunities for youth and young adults with disabilities and their families</li>
  <li>Excellent communication and presentation skills </li>
  <li>Ability to meet timelines, manage multiple tasks, and give attention to details &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </li>
  <li>Ability to work independently and as part of a team</li>
  <li>Proficiency in computer software</li>
  <li>Ability to advocate for individuals with disabilities and their families</li>
  <li>Strong writing skills</li>
  <li>Ability to provide own transportation and flexibility to travel for state and national presentations. Occasional overnight travel will be required.</li>
</ul>

